<div class="quote">
   <p> So this gauze is from our Christmas pantomime from Beauty and the Beast in 2021. The cloth you see is a transformation gauze, different to a normal scenic canvas cloth. We've painted it in dark blues and ultramarine and Prussian colours. There's a large offset silver and gold star and radiating from it is a trail of iridescent bubbles.</p>

<p>The bubbles increase in size as they get further away from the star. Each bubble is individually painted with reflective light and glittered with iridescent glitter. The magic of the transformation gauze is that depending on the way it is lit, it can look solid and at other times see-through. This is achieved by a high level of light directed to the face of the gauze.</p>

<p>If this light is taken away and redirected to something behind the gauze, such as the actors or a different scene, the image on the gauze, in this instance the bubbles and the star, will completely disappear and reveal the scene behind, just like magic.</p>

<p>So this cloth was painted in four days and then taken down and put on the workshop floor for the final day. This allowed us to glitter it flat. It's very difficult to glitter it upright so doing it on the flat is the best way of doing it.</p>

    
</div>
