<p class="bold">Isn't it lush?</p>
<p>This is a relaxed space, for people who need it. I’ve noticed through the years how Theatr Clwyd embraces everyone – whatever your age, ability or circumstance. We’re all part of the family.</p>
<p>This box is at the back of the theatre, at the far right. It has a big rectangular window, looking out at the stage and the gorgeous theatre seats. Hey, audience, we're behind you!</p>
<p>Sorry, I couldn't resist.</p>
<p>Every seat in the theatre – not just this one – has a brilliant view. That care was built into its design. </p>

<p>You might notice the amazing red tiles which line the walls. They have beautiful curved edges, and look almost like bricks. I love looking out at them when I’m on stage. They’ve been here since day one, and they’re one of the things that give this space its special acoustic, bouncing sound around the room.</p>

<p>Ooh, look! There's one of them here for you to touch</p>

